playbook.success_criteria:
Code review sign-off by a peer and a security engineer. Unit and integration tests for authentication, authorization, and input validation logic pass. Example code change (Java Spring Boot): 
```java
// Before (potentially vulnerable input handling)
// String userId = request.getParameter("userId");

// After (with input validation and sanitization)
@PostMapping("/transfer")
@PreAuthorize("hasRole('USER') and @securityService.canAccessAccount(authentication.principal.username, #transferRequest.sourceAccountId)")
public ResponseEntity<String> transferFunds(@Valid @RequestBody TransferRequest transferRequest) {
    // ... business logic ...
}

// Example TransferRequest DTO with validation annotations
public class TransferRequest {
    @NotBlank @Pattern(regexp = "^[0-9]{12}$")
    private String sourceAccountId;
    @Min(1) @Max(1000000)
    private BigDecimal amount;
    // ... other fields ...
}
```

SAST/DAST scans run automatically on every code commit/build. Reports are generated, and critical findings block deployment. Example (Jenkinsfile snippet): 
```groovy
stage('SAST Scan') {
    steps {
        script {
            sh 'sast-tool scan --project CoreBankingAPI --fail-on-critical'
        }
    }
}
stage('DAST Scan') {
    steps {
        script {
            sh 'dast-tool scan --url ${COREBANKING_API_URL} --fail-on-high'
        }
    }
}
```
